  "2026-04-07T18:13:55.809Z",codex-agent,"Duplicate-check evidence: pm context --limit 10; pm list-open --limit 20; pm list-in-progress --limit 20; pm list-blocked --limit 20; pm search 'gc dry-run scope' --limit 10. Net-new because existing gc lineage covers baseline gc and hook dispatch,not no-side-effect preview plus scoped cleanup ergonomics."
  "2026-04-07T18:14:24.799Z",codex-agent,"Execution note: this net-new task isolates gc safety ergonomics (dry-run + scope selectors + guidance output) to avoid mixing with legacy gc hook-dispatch scope and to keep regression tests/docs traceable."
  "2026-04-07T18:57:50.653Z",codex-agent,"Implemented gc safety ergonomics: added --dry-run preview semantics, comma/repeatable --scope selectors (index/embeddings/runtime), runtime scope cleanup target support, and deterministic reindex guidance output. Wired CLI flags, contracts, completion, and Pi wrapper parity; validated with targeted unit+integration suites."
  "2026-04-07T19:28:09.447Z",codex-agent,"Post-verification hardening: fixed full-suite regression in tests/integration/cli.integration.spec.ts for gc retained runtime target expectations and added gc unit coverage for not_a_directory + empty-scope token usage branches to restore 100% coverage thresholds."
